entries.title: The Doll Lab
entries.summary:
(PRODUCER'S CUT)
They gave me the music and with no budget, no time, and no resources I was promptly asked by a producer at a record label to come up with "something". He gave me an artist and three of her tracks to mashup, and my friends (most of whom have never done anything in video before) ran into the woods in 30F-40F foggy weather and came up with this on the spot without even a damn script lol. It was a very fun, challenging weekend. The label doesn't review it until next month.

On our way out of town I picked up an old down feather sleeping bag and some kindergarten fingerpaint, hehe...

Director, Editor - Matthew Brown
Cinematography - Nathan M. Miller
Additional Camera/Camera Assistant - Nicholas Davis
Lighting Design - Nate Redford

Special Thank you to Peter Bergler, Brent Haynes, Ian Todd, and Nathan Miller for your patience and generosity on this crazy little weekend. And sorry to the actors for the being in wet paint in the cold woods.

NOTE: I May or may not be able to edit a version of my own with different music, pace and style for my own portfolio.

entries.title: Hell and Back Again clip
entries.summary:
facebook.com/​HellandBackAgainTheMovie

What does it mean to lead men in war? What does it mean to come home? Hell and Back Again is a cinematically revolutionary film that asks and answers these questions with a power and intimacy no previous film about the conflict in Afghanistan has been able to achieve.

In this groundbreaking work of cinema, two overlapping narratives are brilliantly intercut – the life of a Marine at war on the front, and the life the same Marine in recovery, at home – creating both a dreamlike quality and a strikingly realistic depiction of how Marines experience this war.

Following Sergeant Nathan Harris of Echo Company, 2nd Battalion, 8th Marine Regiment, during a major assault on a Taliban stronghold, and his painful return home after a severe injury, the two stories communicate both the extraordinary drama of war and the no less shocking experience of returning home, as a whole generation of Marines struggle to find an identity in a country that prefers to be indifferent.

Cast: Danfung Dennis

entries.title: Get Back Guinozzi !  " low files tropical "
entries.summary:
Get Back Guinozzi ! " low files tropical " Vidéo by Jean-Luc CHARLES.

Director Jean-Luc Charles is deploying images captured on Super 8 in the early 70's in the middle of bingo, a hedonistic resort situated in Bandol and detained at the time by his dad.
The place took place at the time of disco, bowling, restaurant, residence elegantly erotic target for bombers from the corner, etc.. Another time, therefore, comes back to life during those three minutes widows inhibitions.

Le réalisateur Jean-Luc Charles y déploie des images captées en super 8 ,au début des années 70 au beau milieu du Bingo, un complexe hédoniste sis à Bandol et détenu à l'époque par son papa.
L'endroit tenait lieu à la fois de discothèque, de bowling, de restaurant, de résidence élégamment érotique, de cible pour les plastiqueurs du coin, etc. Un autre temps, donc, qui reprend vie pendant ces trois minutes veuves d'inhibitions.

Cast: Jean-luc Charles

entries.title: Hey Randy, Happy Birthday
entries.summary:
This video is long and boring if you're not Randy, well, even if you are Randy. Nothing really special happens in it other than a series of notes.

Randy's wife, Dana, made a surprise channel for him for his birthday, and had all his friends make videos for him. Needless to say, mine was pretty lame.

However, I thought I'd upload it because it was also a test using my Anamorphic Lens Adapter.

Thanks to my friend Alex who helped me shoot this.
